<i>  where mezcal is made.</i>

40:51.450 --> 40:53.917
Oh, no. A distillery
right there. How 'bout that?

40:53.919 --> 40:55.585
Mezcal everywhere.

40:55.587 --> 40:58.054
I'm getting ready to go down
to see xaime niembro.

40:58.056 --> 41:01.925
Xaime is part owner of
the gracias a dios distillery.

41:01.927 --> 41:03.693
Xaime is going to show me
all about mezcal.

41:03.695 --> 41:05.195
We're in mezcal country.

41:05.197 --> 41:09.098
This is where 90 percent
of mezcal is made
in all of mexico.

41:09.301 --> 41:11.267
There's another distillery.

41:11.269 --> 41:13.036
There's another one there.
Look at that.

41:13.038 --> 41:14.904
I don't know
a lot about mezcal,

41:14.906 --> 41:16.139
you know, I've had it before.

41:16.141 --> 41:17.373
I know it has a smoky taste.

41:17.375 --> 41:19.609
I know it's made from a agave.

41:19.611 --> 41:21.211
And um... You know, it's...

41:21.213 --> 41:24.814
It's... It's like the roots
of mexico, really, you know.

41:24.816 --> 41:26.149
Everything you see here.

41:26.151 --> 41:27.584
Mezcal, mezcal, mezcal.
